# Testing Conventions

## Required: initTestBed() before TestBed

Every spec file must call `initTestBed()` before `TestBed.configureTestingModule()`. This is a compatibility requirement from upstream.

```typescript
import { initTestBed } from '../../testing/utils';

describe('MyComponent', () => {
  beforeEach(async () => {
    initTestBed();  // MUST be called first
    await TestBed.configureTestingModule({
      imports: [MyComponent],
      providers: [
        { provide: AGENT_SERVICE, useClass: MockAgentService },
      ],
    }).compileComponents();
  });
});
```

## Mock services

Use upstream mocks from `src/app/core/services/testing/` for upstream service dependencies. Create enterprise mocks alongside their services.

## Test file placement

- Place `*.spec.ts` next to the file being tested
- Follow the same naming: `my-service.ts` → `my-service.spec.ts`
